---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PrimaryCTA from '../../components/PrimaryCTA.astro';
import { Check, X, ArrowRight } from 'lucide-astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "The Cost of Authority: 2026 Backlink Pricing Index",
  "description": "Research and pricing data on editorial citation acquisition in 2026, published by Ranking Atlas.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Daniel Grainger",
    "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com/about",
    "jobTitle": "Founder",
    "worksFor": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Ranking Atlas",
      "url": "https://ranking-atlas.com"
    },
    "sameAs": [
      "https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-grainger/",
      "https://ranking-atlas.com/about"
    ]
  },
  "datePublished": "2026-03-01",
  "dateModified": "2026-04-01",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Ranking Atlas" }
};
---

<Layout
  title="The Cost of Authority: 2026 Backlink Pricing Index — Ranking Atlas"
  description="Primary-source backlink pricing data for 2026: cost of authority across DR tiers, agency vs publisher-direct rates, and longitudinal pricing trends. Published by Ranking Atlas."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />

  <!-- ── HERO ── -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[800px] h-[600px] rounded-full opacity-[0.10] blur-[140px]"
           style="background: radial-gradient(circle, #5D4FE0 0%, transparent 70%);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.02] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true"
      style="background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 width=%22100%22 height=%22100%22><filter id=%22n%22><feTurbulence type=%22fractalNoise%22 baseFrequency=%220.9%22/></filter><rect width=%22100%22 height=%22100%22 filter=%22url(%23n)%22/></svg>');"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3">2026 Backlink Pricing Index</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-[1.1] mb-6">
        The Cost Of Authority
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-6">
        Backlinks remain one of the strongest ranking signals in search. Yet the market for acquiring them is opaque, fragmented, and rife with inflated metrics.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-[#64748B] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-4">
        This report analyses pricing data from over 140,000 publisher listings across 10 major link marketplaces, cross-referenced with published rates from named service providers and independent industry studies. It examines the cost of link acquisition across four dimensions:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-base text-[#64748B] text-left inline-block mb-6 space-y-1">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><ArrowRight size={16} class="text-[#5D4FE0] shrink-0 mt-0.5" />Domain Rating (DR 10 through DR 80+)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><ArrowRight size={16} class="text-[#5D4FE0] shrink-0 mt-0.5" />Organic traffic (zero-traffic sites through 50,000+ monthly visitors)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><ArrowRight size={16} class="text-[#5D4FE0] shrink-0 mt-0.5" />Niche and industry vertical</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><ArrowRight size={16} class="text-[#5D4FE0] shrink-0 mt-0.5" />Acquisition method (guest posts, niche edits, and earned media through digital PR)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-base text-[#64748B] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        The findings suggest that the majority of marketplace inventory fails basic quality thresholds, that pricing bears limited correlation to actual link value, and that earned media through digital PR delivers a structurally different — and more durable — outcome than purchased links at comparable or lower cost per placement.
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <a href="/about" class="shrink-0">
          <img src="/assets/images/author/daniel-headshot.jpg" alt="Daniel Grainger" class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full object-cover" width="48" height="48" />
        </a>
        <div class="text-left">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">By <a href="/about" class="text-brand hover:text-brand-dark transition-colors">Daniel Grainger</a>, founder of Ranking Atlas</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#64748B]">Published March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Based on 140,000+ publisher listings</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 4 stat cards -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-left">
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)] transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Avg. guest post cost</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0A0F1E] mb-1">$365</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">Direct from publisher</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            The average price a publisher charges for a single guest post placement, bought directly through a marketplace. This is the base cost before any vendor or agency markup.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)] transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Avg. vendor markup</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0A0F1E] mb-1">75%</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">Buying through intermediaries</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            When you buy through an agency or managed service instead of directly on a marketplace, you pay an average of 75% more. A $365 direct placement becomes ~$1,459 through an intermediary.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)] transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Quality-filtered avg.</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0A0F1E] mb-1">$930</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">DR50+ with real traffic</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            When you filter marketplace listings to only include sites with DR50+ and real organic traffic (1,000+ monthly visitors), the average price jumps to $930. Quality links cost far more than the headline average suggests.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 p-6 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)] transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-[0_8px_30px_-8px_rgba(93,79,224,0.2)] hover:border-[#5D4FE0]/20 relative">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-2">Meet quality bar</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0A0F1E] mb-1">4.6%</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#64748B]">Of all marketplace listings</p>
          <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute bottom-full left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mb-2 w-64 bg-[#0A0F1E] text-white text-xs rounded-lg p-3 leading-relaxed z-10 pointer-events-none">
            Of all guest post sites on marketplaces, only 4.6% meet basic quality criteria: minimum DR40 and minimum 1,000 monthly organic traffic. The other 95.4% are unlikely to deliver meaningful SEO value.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── PRICING DATA ── -->
  <section id="data" class="bg-white py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3">Pricing Data</div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-5">
        How Much Guest Posts And Niche Edits Cost In 2026
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-8 font-medium max-w-3xl">
        Marketplace pricing for guest posts and niche edits, broken down by Domain Rating. Prices scale exponentially — a DR80+ placement costs 10–100x more than a DR20.
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)]">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-[#F1F5F9]">
              <th class="text-left px-6 py-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#64748B]">DR range</th>
              <th class="text-left px-6 py-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#64748B]">Guest post</th>
              <th class="text-left px-6 py-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#64748B]">Niche edit</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[#0A0F1E]/6">
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 10–20</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$70–150</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$49–100</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 20–30</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$100–250</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$75–225</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 30–40</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$150–400</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$150–350</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 40–50</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$250–600</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$250–400</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 50–60</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$400–700</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$350–600</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 60–70</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$500–1,000</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$500–700</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 70–80</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$800–2,000</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$700–1,000+</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#F8F7FA]/50 hover:bg-[#F8F7FA] transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-[#0A0F1E]">DR 80+</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$1,500–10,000+</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-mono font-medium text-[#0A0F1E]">$1,000+</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-[#94A3B8] mt-4">Prices reflect direct marketplace rates. Buying through a vendor or managed service typically adds a 75% markup.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── TRAFFIC HEATMAP ── -->
  <section id="heatmap" class="py-16 md:py-24" style="background: #F8F7FA;">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-5">
        Why Domain Rating Alone Is An Unreliable Guide To Pricing
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[#475569] leading-relaxed mb-8 font-medium max-w-3xl">
        DR alone is an unreliable guide to link value. A high-DR site with no traffic may have an inflated rating. This heatmap shows how organic traffic changes the price — and the value — of a link at every DR tier.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-[#0A0F1E]/8 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)] p-6 mb-10 overflow-x-auto">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94A3B8] mb-4">Average guest post price (USD) by DR and monthly organic traffic</p>
        <div id="heatmapEl"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[#5D4FE0] rounded-r-2xl p-6 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)]">
          <p class="text-3xl font-black text-[#5D4FE0] mb-2">19%</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#475569] leading-relaxed">Of marketplace guest post sites receive fewer than 100 monthly organic visitors — yet many still charge mid-tier prices. A $300 link on a zero-traffic DR50 site delivers less value than a $150 link on a DR30 site with 10,000 real visitors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[#5D4FE0] rounded-r-2xl p-6 shadow-[0_4px_20px_-8px_rgba(10,15,30,0.08)]">
          <p class="text-3xl font-black text-[#5D4FE0] mb-2">53%</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#475569] leading-relaxed">Of DR71+ sites on marketplace databases fall into mid- or low-quality categories because they have under 50,000 monthly organic traffic. High DR without traffic is a red flag.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── LONGITUDINAL PRICING ── -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-bg-cream">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-brand font-medium mb-3">Longitudinal Data</div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink leading-tight mb-5">
        How Agency Link Prices Have Changed, 2020–2026
      </h2>
      <p class="text-body text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Primary-source pricing data for five established link-building agencies, extracted from timestamped Wayback Machine snapshots of their public pricing pages. Each data point is a direct observation of what the agency charged in that year, not a secondary-source estimate. DR30+ equivalent shown (the most commonly listed tier across all vendors and years).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-card p-6 md:p-10 mb-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 780 440" class="w-full h-auto" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-labelledby="chart-title chart-desc">
        <title id="chart-title">Agency DR30+ link prices, 2020 to 2026</title>
        <desc id="chart-desc">Line chart showing per-link pricing over time for FATJOE, Searcharoo, Loganix, RhinoRank, and a publisher-direct industry benchmark.</desc>
        <g stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1">
          <line x1="80" y1="60"  x2="740" y2="60"/>
          <line x1="80" y1="124" x2="740" y2="124"/>
          <line x1="80" y1="188" x2="740" y2="188"/>
          <line x1="80" y1="252" x2="740" y2="252"/>
          <line x1="80" y1="316" x2="740" y2="316"/>
          <line x1="80" y1="380" x2="740" y2="380" stroke="#9CA3AF"/>
        </g>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-size="12" fill="#6B7280" text-anchor="end">
          <text x="70" y="64">$250</text>
          <text x="70" y="128">$200</text>
          <text x="70" y="192">$150</text>
          <text x="70" y="256">$100</text>
          <text x="70" y="320">$50</text>
          <text x="70" y="384">$0</text>
        </g>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-size="12" fill="#6B7280" text-anchor="middle">
          <text x="110" y="405">2020</text>
          <text x="215" y="405">2021</text>
          <text x="320" y="405">2022</text>
          <text x="425" y="405">2023</text>
          <text x="530" y="405">2024</text>
          <text x="635" y="405">2025</text>
          <text x="740" y="405">2026</text>
        </g>
        <g stroke="#5D4FE0" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
          <polyline points="110,259 215,276 635,227 740,227"/>
        </g>
        <g fill="#5D4FE0">
          <circle cx="110" cy="259" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="215" cy="276" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="635" cy="227" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="740" cy="227" r="4"/>
        </g>
        <g stroke="#059669" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="6 3">
          <polyline points="110,209 530,124 635,124 740,124"/>
        </g>
        <g fill="#059669">
          <circle cx="110" cy="209" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="530" cy="124" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="635" cy="124" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="740" cy="124" r="4"/>
        </g>
        <g stroke="#DB2777" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
          <polyline points="320,230 635,150"/>
        </g>
        <g fill="#DB2777">
          <circle cx="320" cy="230" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="635" cy="150" r="4"/>
        </g>
        <g stroke="#D97706" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none">
          <polyline points="320,227 740,227"/>
        </g>
        <g fill="#D97706">
          <circle cx="320" cy="227" r="4"/>
          <circle cx="740" cy="227" r="4"/>
        </g>
        <g stroke="#6B7280" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="2 3">
          <polyline points="110,342 530,264"/>
        </g>
        <g fill="#6B7280">
          <circle cx="110" cy="342" r="3"/>
          <circle cx="530" cy="264" r="3"/>
        </g>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-size="13" fill="#374151">
          <g transform="translate(100, 30)">
            <rect width="14" height="3" y="5" fill="#5D4FE0"/>
            <text x="22" y="10">FATJOE</text>
          </g>
          <g transform="translate(200, 30)">
            <line x1="0" y1="6" x2="14" y2="6" stroke="#059669" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="4 2"/>
            <text x="22" y="10">Loganix</text>
          </g>
          <g transform="translate(300, 30)">
            <rect width="14" height="3" y="5" fill="#DB2777"/>
            <text x="22" y="10">Searcharoo</text>
          </g>
          <g transform="translate(420, 30)">
            <rect width="14" height="3" y="5" fill="#D97706"/>
            <text x="22" y="10">RhinoRank</text>
          </g>
          <g transform="translate(540, 30)">
            <line x1="0" y1="6" x2="14" y2="6" stroke="#6B7280" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="2 2"/>
            <text x="22" y="10">Publisher-direct (FatRank)</text>
          </g>
        </g>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-muted italic mb-12">
      Lines connect only the years for which a given vendor has a verified snapshot. Gaps reflect missing Wayback coverage for that URL in that year, not pricing gaps.
    </p>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink leading-snug mb-3">Per-Vendor Pricing, DR30+ Equivalent</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl shadow-card bg-white">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-bg-paper text-ink">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Vendor</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2020</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2021</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2022</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2023</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2024</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2025</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">2026</th>
              <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-brand">Change</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-body divide-y divide-subtle">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">FATJOE</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right">$95</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right">$81</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-muted">—</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-muted">—</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-muted">—</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right">$120</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right">$120</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-medium">+26%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink">Loganix</td>
